         <head>DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY</head>
         <unittitle label="Title:">Gustav Edward Kappler, papers, <unitdate type="inclusive"
               >1951-2014</unitdate>
         </unittitle>
         <unitid label="Collection Number:">7041</unitid>
         <origination label="Creator:">
            <persname normal="Kappler, Gustav Edward, 1940-">Gustav Edward Kappler, 1940-</persname>
         </origination>
         <physdesc label="Quantity:">.8 cubic feet</physdesc>
         <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Photographs, manuscripts, audio recordings,
            ephemera.</physdesc>
         <repository label="Repository:">Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell
            University Library</repository>
         <abstract label="Abstract:">Collection of color slides, tape recordings and transcripts
            describing the vascular surgeon's experiences during the Vietnam War.</abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041"
               langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <bioghist>
         <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
         <p>Gustav Kappler, Cornell University Class of 1961, M.D. 1965, was a vascular surgeon
            during the Vietnam War.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Includes color slides, with a tape recording and transcript describing the slides, 1984;
            also a DVD of a presentation by Dr. Kappler and David Leeser given at Weill Auditorium
            on February 13, 2012 and a DVD with a Powerpoint presentation of the slides. Also tapes
            sent home, telegrams, and correspondence, 1970-1984; photograph albums; Vietnamese
            currency and other memorabilia; and manuscript draft for article.</p>
         <p>Booklet compiled for the 2008 Reunion of staff from the Phu Bai/85th Evacuation
            Hospital, 1971/72, with information about their later lives. Folder of materials from
            the 2010 Reunion, including updates on their lives, CDs with photographs and songs, and
            information about Hilton Head.</p>
      </scopecontent>
